  <span id="freeText14411407327753274135" style="display:none">What a waste of an amazing story on an incapable writer. There is no 'prose', there is really just "he did this, and then he did that". No depth of emotion, no depth of characters, heck - no characters! I couldn't tell you ONE personality trait of Gita's. Lale also, is so thinly drawn I know nothing about him other than he is supposedly charming. <br /><br />The dialogue between characters is ridiculously empty and the whole thing feels like the most superficial experience of Auschwitz possible.<br /><br />The love story, which I'm sure had depth and feeling in real life, is like a disney retelling. <br /><br />A sad sad waste :(</span>
